  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bb0 \u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2 \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b89\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc0\u0bb1\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bc1 : \u0b85\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd : \u0b87\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b89\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Violation Petition against Emergency Act: Ambika filed: Interim injunction also sought",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "A Fundamental Rights Petition has been filed in the High Court seeking an order to quash the Emergency Gazette No. 2289/07 issued by the President under the Public Safety Ordinance.",
        "Advocate Ambika Chargunathan, a former commissioner of the Sri Lanka Human Rights Commission, filed this petition on the 28th.",
        "Instead of the President, the Attorney General, former Secretary to the President Kamini Senarath, current Secretary to the President Saman Ekanayake and Defense Secretary retired General Kamal Gunaratne have been named as defendants.",
        "The petitioner has requested the High Court to declare that the fundamental right guaranteed by the Constitution has been violated by the implementation of the Emergency Act.",
        "Under the Public Safety Ordinance, the emergency law implemented by the President on the 17th nationwide has paved the way for illegal arrests, detentions, torture, etc.",
        "The petitioner stated in the petition that sections 9,11,12,13,14,15,17,18,20,21,26,34,36,37 mentioned in the declaration of emergency are unconstitutional.",
        "The said State of Emergency Proclamation in the Gazette is based on the fundamental rights enshrined in the Constitution viz. 10, 11, 12(1), 12(2), 13(1), 13 (2), 13 (3), 13(4), 13(1) of the Constitution. 5), 14 A, 14(1)a, 14(1)b, 14(1)d, 14(1)a, 14(1)a and also contravenes Articles 4(f) and 111e of the Constitution. The petitioner has also pointed out that the",
        "Therefore, petitioner lawyer Ambika Sargunanathan has requested in a petition to issue an interim order to suspend the gazette containing the emergency orders issued by the President.",
        "Sri Lankan lawyer Ambika Sargunanathan has further requested the High Court to issue an interim order to prevent further orders from being issued by the President or an officer authorized by the President through the said law."
      ],
